name: Lifecycle
label: lifecycle
definition: arrangement that compares the cyclical nature of families, organizations, processes, products, marketing, and order management, portfolio management or other systems with the cradle to grave life stages (birth, growth, maturity, decay, and death) of living organisms

name: LifecycleStageOccurrence
definition: realization of a phase in a given lifecycle
label: lifecycle stage occurrence

name: LifecycleEvent
definition: kind of event that occurs during one or more stages of a lifecycle
label: lifecycle event

name: LifecycleEventOccurrence
definition: realization of an event in a stage of a lifecycle
label: lifecycle event occurrence

name: LifecycleStatus
definition: classifier indicating the position or state of something at a particular point in its life-cycle
label: lifecycle status

name: isStageOf
label: is stage of
definition: relates a stage in a product or trade lifecycle or process to the lifecycle or process that it is a stage of

name: isLifecycleOf
definition: relates a lifecycle to something it characterizes
label: is lifecycle of

name: hasStage
definition: relates something, such as a product or trade lifecycle or related process, to a phase or stage in that lifecycle
label: has stage

name: hasLifecycle
label: has lifecycle
definition: relates something, such as a product, trade, or related process, to a lifecycle that characterizes it
